      "amount": "to taste"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (205°C).",
    "Dice pumpkin, onion, and garlic. Peel ginger.",
    "In a bowl, mix pumpkin, diced onion, chopped garlic, and minced ginger with soy sauce and salt.",
    "Add gluten-free all-purpose flour to the mixture for thickening.",
    "Heat oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add mixed vegetables.",
    "Cook for 5-7 minutes or until onions become translucent. Stir-fry gently.",
    "Transfer the mixture to an oven-safe dish, and bake at 400°F (205°C) for about 15 minutes or until most of liquid evaporates and vegetables are tender.",
    "Garnish with fresh herbs if desired."
  ],
